A simplified version of the [[Huxley-Hodgkin equations]].

V,m evolve on a similar fast timescale.

n,h evolve on a similar slow timescale.

==> Lump together (V,m) into a single activation variable $$V(t)$$, also (n,h) into $$n(t)$$.

After non-dimensionalizing:

$$\epsilon \frac{dV}{dt} = AV(\delta - V)(V-1)-n+I_a$$

$$\frac{dn}{dt}=V-\gamma n$$

$$A, \gamma  = O(1)$$. $$0 <\epsilon\ll \delta \ll 1$$

$$I_a$$ is applied current.

Can analyze in [[Phase plane]]